3. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper uses sonar scans as input to the novelty detection algorithm, which could be considered a form of computer vision. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The algorithm used in the paper involves learning and updating a model of the environment, which is a common task in machine learning. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves developing a real-time novelty detection system for a mobile robot, which could be considered a control system.
